IMMEDIATELY AFTER TAKEOFF, THE PILOT EXPERIENCED AN EXPLOSION IN THE 
TAIL OF THE MIG-17T.  HE RETURNED TO THE FIELD AND THE FIRE WAS 
EXTINGUISHED BY THE FIRE DEPARTMENT.  INSPECTION REVEALED THAT AN 
ALUMINUM FUEL LINE IN THE AFT SECTION HAD EXPERIENCED METALLURGICAL 
FAILURE.  THE OWNER ADVISED ALL OTHER MIG-17 OPERATORS TO REPLACE THAT, 
AND OTHER, FUEL LINES WITH STAINLESS STEEL LINES. 
FAILURE OF A METAL FUEL LINE, RESULTING IN AN EXPLOSION. 
